        %h2 How to Get Money for your Business in the United States
        %img{:class => "float-right", :alt => "esl lessons finance", :src => "https://cdn.gatewaycfs.com/video_pic1.png"}>/
        %p In the United States, you can start a business with someone else’s money. You can go to a bank to get money, or you can ask other people or companies for money. After you start your business, you might still need someone else’s money to keep your business running.
        %p Of course, no one (except maybe friends or family) gives money away for free. When you use someone else’s money, you have to pay more back than you originally received.
        %p The more you study the following words, the better you will do at our games and the better you will understand the process of getting money for your business in the United States!
        %img{:class => "float-right", :alt => "esl lesson games", :src => "https://cdn.gatewaycfs.com/bee-icon.png"}>/
        %p.highlighted Before you take our fill-in-the blank quiz and play our popular game, "Bee the Broker", study the following vocabulary and learn about different types of loans and advances!
  
        
