              %dt capital
              %dd money invested in a business to help it grow
            .drow
              %dt borrow
              %dd to take get something with the agreement to give it back later
            .drow
              %dt loan
              %dd a lender gives money to a borrower, with the agreement that the borrower will repay the money, in most cases with interest
            .drow
              %dt principal
              %dd amount given by the lender
            .drow
              %dt interest
              %dd money paid back in addition to the principal
            .drow
              %dt interest rate
              %dd interest expressed as percentage of principal
            .drow
              %dt collateral
              %dd something with value (e.g. car, house, etc.) that lender can take if borrower cannot pay back loan
            .drow
              %dt fee
              %dd money paid for a service; extra charge
            .drow
              %dt fixed rate
              %dd loan agreement in which interest remains the same throughout repayment period
            .drow
              %dt variable rate
              %dd loan agreement in which interest payments are adjusted according to certain conditions
            .drow
              %dt repayment period
              %dd amount of time agreed upon that loan should be paid off
            .drow
              %dt APR (annual percentage rate)
              %dd interest rate calculated over one year
            .drow
              %dt credit score
              %dd a number between 300 and 850 that reflects how good your credit is; generally above 700 is a good score
            .drow
              %dt credit history
              %dd record of debt over time; measures amount of borrowing and how you’ve paid off debt
            .drow
              %dt startup
              %dd a small company starting an original type of business
            .drow
              %dt B2B
              %dd business-to-business; a business that sells to other businesses
            .drow
              %dt B2C
              %dd business-to-consumer;  a business that sells directly to consumers
            .drow
              %dt cash flow
              %dd amount of cash available for use
            .drow
              %dt factoring
              %dd selling of unpaid invoices at a discount in exchange for immediate cash flow
            .drow
              %dt accounts receivable
              %dd money owed to a company by its debtors; invoices from customers that have NOT been paid
            .drow
              %dt advance
              %dd amount paid or received before the agreed upon action is completed
